description:
Discover

Donna White has awoken into a completely new world. Freed from the Gloom and at the rebel camp she is learning that everything she thought was important just doesn't matter. But the dark forces of the Gloom want them all back inside, and are willing to kill to make it happen. A sunrise, a funeral, a keytar, and revelations in Rainbow in the Dark's second explosive issue.
name: Discover

description: Reprints the first appearances of the Silver Surfer and Galactus from Fantastic Four (Vol. 1) 48, 49, & 50.
name: The Coming of Galactus

volume.name: Silver Surfer: The Coming of Galactus

name: The Trail of the Terrible Rockets

description: Passion Fruit is a unique, unforgettable collection of stories that examines our innermost secrets and hidden desires. Here, two female cousins learn that living together may bring them closer to each other...or drive them apart; two friends discover the true meaning of loving yourself; twin brothers share nearly everything, even their nightmarish visions; and a woman's heartbreaking love affair unfolds in silent, breathtaking images. With uninhibited authenticity and pathos, Passion Fruit explores the vulnerability and frailty of the human condition.
name: Sweat & Honey

description: Passion Fruit is a unique, unforgettable collection of stories that examines our conflicting desire for change in the strange and unusual world we call home. Here, a young girl in an isolated town has an out-of-the-ordinary experience; a surfer and his gal make waves in their turbulent relationship; and a boy and his twin sister must deal with feelings of being abandoned. With an uncompromising blend of realism and raw emotion, passion is stranger than fiction!
name: Galaxy Girl, Panda Boy

description: Collects 12 short stories with “dickgirls” as the primary theme. Futanari Clinic – Doctor and nurse tests out their patient’s new bodypart before she leaves the hospital. Kannagi – a shrine maiden is possessd by a demon who must be exorcized through her new well-endowed penis.
name: Vol. 1

description: When childhood innocence gives way to a blinding thirst for revenge, is it worth the price of one's humanity? Tetsunosuke and Tatsunosuke are the sons of a diplomat who sought to bring peace and prosperity to Japan during the early Meiji Restoration. But when their parents are murdered before their very eyes, Tetsu seeks to join the Shinsengumi, the unofficial police who are capable of the same brutality as his parents' murderers. Wading through a sea of espionage, deception and bloodshed, the young boy must choose: should he take a step on the path to becoming a demon...or give up his rage and transform into the ultimate Peacemaker?
name: Vol. 1

description: 3 graphic novellas by master BDSM artist Gorou Horikawa. Kaede’s Sword: A young swordswoman crosses a yakuza gang, who then kidnaps and sexually humiliates her. The Young Bride: a dutiful daughter gives up her virginity to help save her father’s faltering business.
name: Vol. 1

description:
Winner of Tokyopop's Rising Stars of Manga competition! Amanda is a lonely 9-year-old girl whose mother agrees to let her have a pet. Amanda chooses a ferret because ferrets aren't ordinary...and neither is she! But there are two big rules: Amanda has to care for Peach, and Peach can't ever bite Amanda. It seems like Amanda finally has the friend she needed. But Peach sees Amanda's hands as five-serpent monsters--and bites in defense! What will little, lonely Amanda do now?! Features the first-ever scratch-and-sniff, peach-scented cover!

Lonely nine-year-old Amanda Keller has persuaded her mother to let her buy a pet! But instead of a dog or cat, Amanda makes a daring decision and comes home with a sleepy little ferret she names Peach.

The arrival of Peach throws a monkey wrench into the previously ordered existence of the Keller household. Peach believes herself to be royalty, since she was worshiped by the ferrets at the pet store. But now Peach lives in fear of Amanda's hands--or as she sees them, the dreaded Handra monster! And her only means of defending herself is to bite!

Nevertheless, when we last left Peach and Amanda, they were able to put aside their differences and call a truce. But Peach is about to discover the world of terror known as Show and Tell...and meet a ferret even more bossy and conceited than she is! Will Princess Peach finally be put in her place?
name: Vol. 1

description: The epic adventure of a ferret who defied her cage continues! It's an exciting day of show-and-tell, and Amanda unveils Peach--to rounds of applause and sky-rocketing approval. But the reaction gives Amanda a twinge of jealousy toward Peach - the kids are only interested in her ferret and not her!
name: Vol. 2

description: Peach continues to wreak havoc trying to escape, and Mimi suggests that maybe Peach is just in need of a playmate. So Amanda and her mom buy her a friend--Prince Edwin! But Prince Edwin is not what Peach expected. Clumsy, ill-mannered, and a little crazy, he hardly lives up to his stately moniker. Will the two be able to forge a friendship, or will they kill each other first?
name: Vol. 3

description: When childhood innocence gives way to a blinding thirst for revenge, is it worth the price of one's humanity? As Vice Commander Hijikata's page, Tetsu is one step closer to becoming a full-fledged member of the ruthless Shinsengumi and to avenging his parents' murders. Yet Tetsu has a few reservations about his decision to commit his life to the unofficial police force--primarily, the Code of the Shinsengumi, a collection of unforgiving samurai laws that require ritual suicide for offenses and prevent Tetsu from ever leaving once he joins. Before he can chose, however, his enemies will force his hand...
name: Vol. 2

description: The Shinsengumi's enemies, the Choushuu, are scheming to restore the emperor to power. But the Shinsengumi are aware of the plot, masterminded by pyromaniac ronin Yoshida Toshimaro. As each side conspires to take action against the other, a secret is revealed about the man who may have killed Tetsu's parents...
name: Vol. 3

description: The hearts of the Shinsengumi are heavy after the death of Ayumu at the hands of the Choushuu rebels. In an act of retaliation, the Shinsengumi storm the rebel's hideout and unleash a mighty slaughter. But while the Shinsengumi nab the master of Masuya, the real culprit, Yoshida, has cornered our hero Tetsu, and begins a nightmarish re-enactment of his parents' murderers... Will Tetsu finally put on the uniform of the Shinsengumi and join the fight?
name: Vol. 4

description: After first foiling a plot by the Choushuu rebels to burn Kyoto to the ground, the Shinsengumi storm the Ikedaya Inn and begin a bloody elimination of the criminal nest there. In the middle of the carnage, Tetsunosuke once again comes face to face with the man who murdered his parents. Will he finally get his revenge? The battle has been won, but the war is far from over...
name: Vol. 5

description: Hurg and his secret organization have been dragged into the open and exposed. Now is the time to strike! Haunt and the agency must act now—before he moves deeper underground. He had Kurt killed, he set these events leading to the birth of Haunt into motion—and now it’s time to pay for what he’s done!
